## Early game

**Naeglar** on Eris (Hive) is the only documented Mutagen Sample source on
the planet: the wiki's drop tables show a Rotation B Hive Sabotage resource
cache with roughly a 15.5% chance for 3 samples. That cache rolls from a
reward table rather than enemy kills, so a Resource Drop Booster and the Steel
Path passive don't affect it — the cache itself is the farm. Clear the Hive
efficiently, bank the Rotation B reward, and reset.

## Mid & late game

Since Eris doesn't have a second Mutagen Sample node, the endgame upgrade is
running **Naeglar** (Hive, Steel Path) with a full 4-player squad instead of
solo. Each player's own mission completion rolls the resource cache table
independently, so a full squad multiplies the number of caches found per run.
Because those caches are reward tables rather than enemy drops, boosters and
the Steel Path passive still don't change the per-cache odds — squad size, not
drop-chance buffs, is what scales this farm. (Deimos' Formido has a similar
cache for players who've reached the Cambion Drift, but Eris is the
self-contained option for this planet's farming path.)

